item.title: [PI] Problem With Running Server
item.dc:creator: @Brandon0044 Brandon0044
item.description:
@Brandon0044 wrote:

Loveandpower:

major minor is thrown when your running on an older java version then the java files were compiled on. This is easily resolved by just going to the newest java version and recompiling/running your server.

Ohhhh…

I had the latest version of Java on my computer, but I never changed the location of it. Didn’t think it would be so obvious. Thanks.

@OP you need to post the contents of your .Batch file you’re running.

Here’s the .batch file.

@echo off title DivineLegacy "C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jre6\bin\java.exe" -Xmx800m -cp bin;deps/poi.jar;deps/mysql.jar;deps/mina.jar;deps/slf4j.jar;deps/slf4j-nop.jar;deps/jython.jar;log4j-1.2.15.jar; server.Server pause

Shouldn’t be misinforming people though. I know it worked but she should be aware that the message is warning her about something, not that the message is secret computer code for IT WORKED.

He*, him*. Thanks for the info, though.
[/quote]

Try this:

title DivineLegacy
“C:\Program Files (x86)\Java\jre6\bin\java.exe” -Xmx800m -cp bin;deps/poi.jar;deps/mysql.jar;deps/mina.jar;deps/slf4j.jar;deps/slf4j-nop.jar;deps/jython.jar;log4j-1.2.15.jar; -cp .; server.Server
